snippet: During the last day of a two-day hearing, prosecutors argued that failing to send Julian Assange to Sweden in a sexual misconduct case would “undermine” the extradition system in Europe.
abstract: Prosecutors argue for the extradition of WikiLeaks founder, Julian Assange, to Sweden in a sexual misconduct case during the last day of a two-day hearing in Great Britain; warn that failing to send him abroad would 'undermine' the extradition system in Europe.
lead_paragraph: During the last day of a two-day hearing, prosecutors argued that failing to send Julian Assange to Sweden in a sexual misconduct case would “undermine” the extradition system in Europe.
